The paper deals with the theory and algorithms for finite tree automata, which are commonly used in formal language theory and verification. The paper discusses the optimization of the textbook algorithm for determinisation and completion of finite tree automata, which is relevant to the sub-category of formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also mentions applications of the algorithm in static analysis of term rewriting systems and logic programs, which are relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The algorithmic optimization involves generating transitions in a compact form, which is relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions checking containment of languages defined by tree automata, which is relevant to the sub-category of symbolic computation (cs.SC).
